<p>Only 20% of dental practices use email marketing. The other 80% rely on phone calls and postcards to fill chairs. Meanwhile, email marketing delivers $36 to $44 in return for every $1 spent, according to <a href="https://www.sixthcitymarketing.com/2024/02/28/dental-marketing-stats/">Sixth City Marketing</a>.</p>
<p>Email marketing for dentists is the most cost-effective way to reduce no-shows, reactivate lapsed patients, and keep your schedule full. Hygiene recall emails alone book 26% of overdue appointments. Reactivation campaigns convert 10 to 12% of inactive patients. Drip follow-up sequences retain 33% more patients annually, per <a href="https://gitnux.org/marketing-in-the-dental-industry-statistics/">Gitnux dental marketing data</a>.</p>
<p>The challenge: dental email marketing has HIPAA requirements that most marketing guides ignore. Sending the wrong type of email without proper consent can result in fines up to $50,000 per violation.</p>
<p>This guide covers the email campaigns that fill dental chairs, the compliance rules you must follow, and the metrics that prove ROI. We publish 3,500+ articles across 70+ industries at Stacc, including dental and healthcare practices.</p>
